<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Presage1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Presage,</orth> subst. <emph>(présage or preságe),</emph> 1) prognostic: <bibl n="shak. ven 457" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 457</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 2, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.158" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 158</bibl>.<lb />2) foreboding, presentiment: <cit><quote>the sad augurs mock their own p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 107.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 107, 6</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if heart's p. be not vain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.142" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 142</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>